"I realized as a white South African doctor, I had access to the best treatment. I realized how extremely lucky I was," Dr. Dalene von Delft, who recovered from multi-drug resistant tuberculosis, said.

Her recovery pushed her to start @TBProof and inspire others. @hari reports. https://t.co/Imr860UgyS

Multi-drug resistant tuberculosis, or MDR, is especially dangerous. Properly treated, TB is curable. But the antibiotics that usually do the trick, don't work against MDR. The strain has evolved to be resistant against standard drugs.
